S.U.B.L.I.M.E. =
Sublime's unsupervised bifurcation: let's infer minimal explanations.

OPTIONS: 

-Max       max numbers to keep           : 512  
-Some      find `far` in this many egs   : 512  
-cautious  On any crash, stop+show stack : False    
-data      data file                     : data/auto93.csv   
-enough    min leaf size                 : .5
-help      show help                     : False  
-far       how far to look in `Some`     : .9  
-p         distance coefficient          : 2  
-seed      random number seed            : 10019  
-todo      start up task                 : nothing  
-xsmall    Cohen's small effect          : .35

See Also

issues :: repo :: view source

Algorithm

Stochastic clustering to generate tiny models. Uses random projections to divide the space. Then, optionally, explain the clusters by unsupervised iterative dichotomization using ranges that most distinguish sibling clusters.

Example1: just bi-cluster on two distant points

sublime.demo.doc: Maybe run a demo, if we want it, resetting random seed first.

sublime.file.doc: Iterator. Returns one row at a time, as cells.

sublime.merge.doc: While we can find similar adjacent things, merge them.

sublime.o.doc: Class that can pretty print its slots, with fast inits.

sublime.options.doc: Convert doc to options dictionary using command line args. Args canuse two 'shorthands': (1) boolean flags have no arguments (and mentioning those on the command line means 'flip the default value'; (2) args need only mention the first few of a key (e.g. -s is enough to select for -seed).

sublime.rN.doc: Round a list of numbers to three decimals.

sublime.Span.doc: Given two Samples and some x range lo..hi, a Span holds often that range appears in each Sample.

sublime.Span.add.doc: y is a label identifying, one Sample or another.

sublime.Span.merge.doc: If the merged span is simpler, return that merge.

sublime.Span.selects.doc: True if the range accepts the row.

sublime.Span.sort.doc: Good spans have large support and low diversity.

sublime.Sym.add.doc: Update symbol counts in has, updating mode as we go.

sublime.Sym.mid.doc: Return central tendancy of this distribution (using mode).

sublime.Sym.spans.doc: For each symbol in i and j, count the number of times we see it on either side.

sublime.Num.add.doc: Reservoir sampler. If _all is full, sometimes replace an item at random.

sublime.Num.div.doc: Report the diversity of this distribution (using standard deviation). ±2, 2,56, 3 σ is 66,90,95%, of the mass. 28σ. So one standard deviation is (90-10)th divide by 2.4 times σ.

sublime.Num.mid.doc: Return central tendency of this distribution (using median).

sublime.Num.spans.doc: Divide the whole space lo to hi into, say, xsmall=16 bin, then count the number of times we the bin on other side. Then merge similar adjacent bins.

sublime.Explain.doc: Tree with yes,no branches for samples that do/do not match a span.

sublime.Cluster.doc: Tree with left,right samples, broken at median between far points.

sublime.Sample.doc: Load, then manage, a set of examples.

sublime.Sample.cluster.doc: Split the data using random projections. Find the span that most separates the data. Divide data on that span.

sublime.Sample.half.doc: Using two faraway points x,y break data at median distance.

sublime.Sample.proj.doc: Find the distance of a row on a line between x and y.

sublime.Sample.xplain.doc: Split the data using random projections. Find the span that most separates the data. Divide data on that span.
